SIMPLE: prompt
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prompt
<hw>Prompt</hw> <pr>(pr⟦ocr⟧mt; 215)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Prompter</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Promptest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>prompt</ets>, L. <ets>promptus</ets>, properly, brought forth (to
light or view), hence, visible, evident, at hand, ready, quick, -- p. p.
of <ets>promere</ets> to take or bring forth; <ets>pro</ets> forth +
<ets>emere</ets> to take. See <er>Redeem</er>. ]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Ready and quick to act as occasion demands; meeting
requirements readily; not slow, dilatory, or hesitating in decision or
action; responding on the instant; immediate; <as>as, <ex>prompt</ex> in
obedience or compliance</as>; -- said of persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Very discerning and <qex>prompt</qex> in giving orders.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Tell him I am <qex>prompt</qex>⟦br⟧
To lay my crown at's feet.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And you, perhaps, too <qex>prompt</qex> in your replies.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Done or rendered quickly, readily, or immediately;
given without delay or hesitation; -- said of conduct; <as>as,
<ex>prompt</ex> assistance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When Washington heard the voice of his country in distress,⟦br⟧
his obedience was <qex>prompt</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ames.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Easy; unobstructed.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The reception of the light into the body of the building was very
<qex>prompt</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir H. Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Ready; expeditious; quick; agile; alert; brisk;
nimble.</syn> <usage> -- <er>Prompt</er>, <er>Ready</er>,
<er>Expeditious</er>. One who is <xex>ready</xex> is prepared to act at
the moment. One who is <xex>prompt</xex> acts at the moment. One who is
<xex>expeditious</xex> carries through an undertaking with constant
promptness.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prompt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prompt
<hw>Prompt</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>A limit of time
given for payment of an account for produce purchased, this limit
varying with different goods. See <er>Prompt-note</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To cover any probable difference of price which might arise before
the expiration of the <qex>prompt</qex>, which for this article [tea] is
three months.</q> <rj><qau>J. S. Mill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prompt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Prompt
<hw>Prompt</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Prompted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Prompting</conjf>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To assist or induce the action of; to move to
action; to instigate; to incite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God first . . . <qex>prompted</qex> on the infirmities of the
infant world by temporal prosperity.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To suggest; to dictate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And whispering angles <qex>prompt</qex> her golden dreams.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To remind, as an actor or an orator, of words or
topics forgotten.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prompt-book</ent>⟦br⟧
